Name: Got Guts Tiger Nuts
Short description:
Our ancestors were crazy about tiger nuts and so are we! Tiger nuts (Cyperus esculentus), sometimes called almonds or chufa, are not really nuts at all but tubers with a full and slightly sweet taste. The tiger nut is one of the oldest cultivated plants and was eaten as early as the Stone Age. Today it makes a comeback as a useful snack - and it's well worth it! A handful of tiger nuts is a perfect snack for both adults and children and is easy to take with you on the trip, to work or to the gym.

- Nut
-free -gluten-free
- Rich in fiber

Our Got Guts Tiger Nuts are grown in sunny West Africa and then peeled and roasted with a special technique so that the taste of the nut's inner core comes into its own.

The packaging can be resealed to keep the contents fresh.

All products are of the highest quality and are sorted and packaged in Sweden.
Description: Tiger nuts are rich in nutrients beneficial for the digestive system and are used by many to relieve symptoms of irritable bowels, stomach cramps and other digestive disorders. Grown in sunny West Africa, these little tubers have been  processed with a special technique to remove their hard outer shell, then roasted to perfection to bring out the full flavour of the nut’s inner core. Tiger nuts are a clean food that goes well with paleo, nut-free and other specialty diets.
